### Revised Abstract Plan

1. We know that for any `r ∈ state.requests.val`, `r.1` (i.e., the `RequestId`) is in `reqIds state.requests`.
2. Similarly, for any `r ∈ requests'.val`, `r.1` is in `reqIds requests'`.
3. For any `r ∈ state.removed`, there exists a corresponding entry in `state.requests.val` (since `r` was previously in `state.requests`).
